strings:
Checking SD card...
Please do not remove the SD card.

There is no SD card in the SD card slot.
Please turn the system off and insert an SD card.

Unable to detect SD card.
Please turn the system off, remove and then re-insert the SD card.

The SD card is write-protected.
Please turn the system off, move the write<->protection switch to the unlocked position and then re-insert the SD card.

There are no photographs on the SD card.
Take some photos by pressing the START button when in a town, a cave or out in the field.

No extra data exists on the SD card.
Please go back to the title screen and create some extra data.

There is not enough free space on the SD card.
Please turn the system off and delete any unwanted data.

The SD card was removed while being written to.
Please turn the system off and re-insert the SD card.
An error occurred while the SD card was being written to. Please turn the system off and re-insert the SD card.

The extra data on the SD card is corrupted.
Please go back to the title screen and create the extra data again.
The extra data on the SD card is not for use with this software. Please go back to the title screen and create the necessary extra data.

This title cannot be played without extra data.
The extra data stores photos you take in the game and postcards you receive from other players.
The extra data created previously by this title cannot be found on this SD card.

The extra data is corrupted.
This title cannot be played without functioning extra data.

This SD card contains extra data created on another system or on another SD card.
The game cannot be played with this extra data.
Overwriting the extra data will mean you are no longer able to view any photos you have taken or postcards you have received. Proceed?

Now creating the extra data...
Please do not remove the SD card / Game Card
or turn off the system.
Please close the software or turn the system off.
In order to use StreetPass, you must agree to the terms of the most up-to-date Nintendo 3DS Service User Agreement and Privacy Policy.

In order to connect to the Internet, you must agree to the terms of the most up-to-date Nintendo 3DS Service User Agreement and
Privacy Policy.
View the Nintendo 3DS Service User Agreement and Privacy Policy?

You will be unable to use StreetPass as you have not agreed to the terms of the Nintendo 3DS Service User Agreement and Privacy Policy.
You will now return to the game.
You will be unable to connect to the Internet as you have not agreed to the terms of the Nintendo 3DS Service User Agreement and Privacy Policy. You will now return to the game.

Saving your game progress...
Please do not turn off the system or remove the SD card / Game Card.

Game progress saved.
Be sure to check out any postcards that you have received.
Failed to save adventure log or quick save log.

Successfully disconnected.
Be sure to check out any postcards that you have received.

Unable to connect as the time and/or date has been changed.
Please wait a day and then try again.
There was a problem with the network connection, so you have been disconnected.

Unable to connect to server.
Please wait a while and then try again.
Connection aborted.

Online Interaction has been restricted by
‘Parental Controls’.

Failed to upload save data.
Please wait a while, then reconnect and try to upload it again.
